docs/combat_authority_map.md:107:- The correct Holy Support proof is the custom-signal blueprint seam plus canonical kernel state/events/snapshots, not a restored `HolySupportAffordance` API.
docs/combat_authority_map.md:112:The current source of truth is split across declarative data (`src/data/skills_ron.rs`, `src/data/units_ron.rs`), shared runtime action processing (`src/combat/turn_system/mod.rs`, `src/combat/turn_system/pipeline.rs`, `src/combat/resolution.rs`), seeded per-Digimon blueprint dispatch (`src/combat/blueprints/mod.rs`, `src/combat/blueprints/patamon.rs`), shared kernel transitions (`src/combat/kernel.rs`), shared mechanic hooks (`src/combat/twin_core.rs`, `src/combat/battery_loop.rs`, `src/combat/holy_support.rs`, `src/combat/predator_loop.rs`, `src/combat/precision_mind_game.rs`), observation surfaces (`src/combat/observability.rs`), and CLI consumption (`src/bin/combat_cli.rs`).
docs/combat_authority_map.md:114:S03 normalized the highest-risk local drift by making beats/kernel transitions live and seeding the Patamon Holy Support blueprint path. S04 closes the presentation metadata boundary by proving `animation_sequence`, `qte`, beat metadata wording, and presentation triggers remain non-authoritative while canonical events, typed custom signals, blueprint dispatch, kernel transitions, and snapshots remain the authority surfaces. Full blueprint migration or full CLI presentation proof remain explicit downstream boundaries.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S04/tasks/T02-PLAN.md:11:Executor setup: load `write-docs`, `api-design` for contract honesty, `design-an-interface` only as a check against inventing a premature presentation-runtime API, and `verify-before-complete`. The doc reader is a future engineer adding UI/CLI presentation cues or new RON metadata; after reading, they should know which surfaces may consume presentation data and which surfaces remain gameplay-authoritative.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S04/tasks/T02-PLAN.md:14:1. Add a concise `docs/presentation_metadata_boundary.md` that states the invariant cold: RON may carry animation/QTE/presentation trigger strings, but gameplay outcomes are decided by effects, typed custom signals, per-Digimon Rust blueprints, kernel transitions, canonical events, and state/snapshot appliers.
