.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S04/tasks/T01-SUMMARY.md:21:Created `tests/presentation_metadata_boundary.rs` with local helpers adapted from the existing Patamon blueprint seam and event stream tests. The new tests parse tracked `assets/data/skills.ron` to contrast `patamon_ult` typed custom signals with metadata-only `agumon_ult` and metadata-free `holy_breeze`; compare action-query affordances and `ResolvedAction` payloads for equivalent skills with and without dramatic presentation metadata; verify malformed command-like animation/QTE strings do not create blueprint transitions; and run paired headless Bevy apps through `register_combat_kernel_runtime` to prove runtime events, canonical lifecycle beats, mirrored kernel beat transitions, Holy Support state, and validation snapshots remain unchanged by misleading presentation metadata. During verification I corrected one over-specific assertion that assumed runtime damage event amount equals raw base damage; the final test now compares equivalent runtime event streams and separately asserts damage/cast event presence.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S04/tasks/T01-SUMMARY.md:25:Ran Rust formatting for the new test file, then ran the slice-level command `cargo test --test presentation_metadata_boundary --test event_stream --test patamon_blueprint_seam` after the final edit. The command exited 0: `event_stream` passed 1/1, `patamon_blueprint_seam` passed 7/7, and `presentation_metadata_boundary` passed 4/4. The new runtime test directly observes `OnCombatBeat`, mirrored `CombatKernelTransition::Beat`, skill-cast/damage events, absence of synthetic `CombatKernelTransition::HolySupport`, default `HolySupportState`, and unchanged validation snapshot text.
