docs/skill_legality_contract.md:3:This document is the R084 contract for combat action legality. It defines the shared vocabulary that later M012 slices must implement in data and code so UI, CLI, AI, tests, and engine validation all ask the same question: given skill data plus a combat world snapshot, what can this actor do, what targets are legal, what resources are ready, and what mechanics are actually implemented?
docs/skill_legality_contract.md:10:- Keep machine-readable reason codes stable across UI, CLI, AI, tests, logs, and engine rejection.
docs/skill_legality_contract.md:23:Skill data owns skill intent: cost, action kind, target shape, effect list, and any explicit legality metadata added by later slices. Combat world snapshot data owns mutable state: phase, active unit, team, HP/KO state, stun state, SP pool, ultimate charge, toughness affordance, implementation declarations, and future mechanic declarations.
docs/skill_legality_contract.md:28:2. A world snapshot extracted from combat state.
docs/skill_legality_contract.md:101:- `TargetNotFound` â€” target identity is absent from the snapshot.
docs/skill_legality_contract.md:109:- `NoValidTargets` â€” the action has no legal targets in the current snapshot.
docs/skill_legality_contract.md:160:1. UI, CLI, AI, tests, and engine validation must consume the same query output.
