.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S03/S03-SUMMARY.md:84:**S03 established and verified the first executable per-Digimon blueprint seam: Patamon RON custom signals now flow through ResolvedAction into a Patamon Rust blueprint, then through generic kernel transitions, canonical events, Holy Support state, and validation snapshots.**
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S03/S03-SUMMARY.md:88:S03 consumed the S02 authority map and drift ledger and normalized the highest-risk local combat authority drift toward the agreed path `RON custom signals -> per-Digimon blueprint Rust module -> generic kernel hooks -> canonical state/events/snapshots`. The slice first repaired S03-owned test fixture drift without restoring obsolete Holy Support APIs (`Effect::HolySupportTag`, `Effect::HolySupportRequest`, or `TargetShape::SelfTarget`) and refreshed Twin Core tests onto the current hook-driven state vocabulary. It then made the kernel runtime participate in real headless paths by registering existing mechanic appliers for the app and combat CLI, while the action pipeline now emits live lifecycle `OnCombatBeat` and `OnKernelTransition::Beat` events directly from deterministic resolution.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S03/S03-SUMMARY.md:92:The first concrete blueprint layer now lives in `src/combat/blueprints/`. The generic router only dispatches wrapper custom-signal metadata, while `src/combat/blueprints/patamon.rs` owns Patamon-specific interpretation and translates `BuildHolySupportGrace` into generic `CombatKernelTransition::HolySupport(HolySupportTransition::build_grace(amount))`. The live pipeline emits blueprint transitions only after successful action resolution, preserving failed-action semantics and keeping registry fanout plus `OnKernelTransition` events canonical. Tests prove the full seed chain: parsed tracked RON signal, copied `ResolvedAction` metadata, Patamon blueprint transition mapping, registry-dispatched `OnKernelTransition`, applied Holy Support state, and `format_validation_snapshot` output.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S03/S03-SUMMARY.md:94:Docs and verifiers were refreshed to reflect the implemented seam. `docs/combat_authority_map.md` now describes the seeded flow and marks it as a seed rather than a full one-module-per-Digimon migration. `docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md` marks local drift items normalized or partially normalized and preserves follow-up boundaries for S04 presentation metadata, S05 CLI proof, and S06 final suite closure. `scripts/verify_combat_authority_audit.py` now checks claim-scoped evidence instead of broad keyword presence, and `docs/m015_failure_ledger.md` plus `scripts/verify_m015_failure_ledger.py` record that remaining `cargo test --no-run` failures are broad fixture/schema, docs, and consumer proof blockers outside S03's targeted authority proof.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S03/S03-SUMMARY.md:98:Fresh completion verification was run after the final metadata updates with `cargo test --test patamon_blueprint_seam --test holy_support_resolution --test holy_support_roster_contract --test holy_support_affordance --test event_stream --test twin_core_mechanics --test twin_core_integration --test validation_snapshot --test battery_loop_kernel --test predator_loop_kernel && python3 scripts/verify_combat_authority_audit.py && python3 scripts/verify_m015_failure_ledger.py` and exited 0. The stdout shows all targeted Rust test binaries passing: battery_loop_kernel 5/5, event_stream 1/1, holy_support_affordance 4/4, holy_support_resolution 2/2, holy_support_roster_contract 4/4, patamon_blueprint_seam 7/7, predator_loop_kernel 7/7, twin_core_integration 1/1, twin_core_mechanics 1/1, validation_snapshot 5/5. Both `Combat authority audit verification passed.` and `M015 failure ledger verification passed.` were printed. Observability surfaces verified by tests include live `OnCombatBeat`, `OnKernelTransition`, Holy Support snapshot state, rejected transition snapshot state, and runtime registration of all kernel domains. Known non-S03 blocker: `cargo test --no-run` still exits 101 and is classified in `docs/m015_failure_ledger.md` as S06/S05 follow-up work for broad fixture/schema drift, missing UI readiness docs, and CLI/consumer proof; this slice does not claim whole-suite closure.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S03/S03-SUMMARY.md:106:- R093 â€” Clear local combat authority drift from the S02 ledger was normalized or explicitly bounded: runtime registration, live beat/kernel events, custom-signal propagation, Patamon blueprint dispatch, Holy Support snapshots, and claim-scoped audit verification all pass.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S03/S03-SUMMARY.md:107:- R094 â€” Tracked Patamon RON custom signal flows through `ResolvedAction` into `src/combat/blueprints/patamon.rs`, then emits generic Holy Support kernel transitions observed via events, state, and validation snapshots.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S03/S03-SUMMARY.md:129:`cargo test --no-run` still exits 101 due to classified broad-suite fixture/schema, missing docs, and consumer/CLI proof blockers recorded in `docs/m015_failure_ledger.md`. The Patamon seam is a seed, not a complete per-Digimon blueprint migration. S04 still needs to harden presentation beat metadata as non-authoritative; S05 still needs to prove CLI shared surfaces; S06 still owns final whole-suite closure.
.gsd/milestones/M015/slices/S03/S03-SUMMARY.md:133:S04: prove presentation beat/trigger metadata cannot become gameplay authority. S05: run the CLI proof through shared action query, event, beat, kernel-observable state, and snapshot surfaces with no CLI-only combat logic. S06: repair/classify remaining broad-suite `cargo test --no-run` blockers and package truthful M013/M015 closure artifacts. Future architecture: migrate additional Digimon behavior into per-Digimon blueprint modules only when there is concrete behavior to own, keeping RON declarative and the kernel generic.
